ers could be recipients of the Torah. On the other hand, some nations were regarded by earlier biblical authors as archenemies of Israel, and these anti-elect people caused also Ben Sira’s anger to be provoked. Ben Sira was deeply rooted in Judaism but this did not prevent him from being open toward foreign influences as far as they were compatible with his religious and cultural heritage.  aIssued also in print.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 01. Dez 2022) 0aGentiles in the Old Testament. 4aApokryphe Literatur. 4aBen Sira. 4aHellenismus. 4aJuden und die Völker. 4aWeisheitsliteratur. 7aRELIGION / Biblical Criticism & Interpretation / Old Testament.2bisacsh  aApocrypha.  aBen Sira.  aHellenism.  aJews and Gentiles.  aWisdom Literature.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDGBA Backlist Complete English Language 2000-2014 PART1z978311023857008iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDGBA Backlist Theology and Religious Studies 2000-2014 (EN)z978311023854908iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDGBA Theology and Religious Studies 2000 - 2014z9783110638165oZDB-23-GTR08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertE-BOOK GESAMTPAKET / COMPLETE PACKAGE 2012z9783110288995oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertE-BOOK PACKAGE THEOLOGY, JUDAISM, RELIGION  2012z978311029384508iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertE-BOOK PAKET THEOLOGIE,RELIGIONSWISS., JUDAISTIK  2012z9783110288957oZDB-23-DGF0 cprintz978311027010540uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978311027011240uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9783110270112423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9783110270112/original  a978-3-11-023854-9  DGBA Backlist Theology and Religious Studies 2000-2014 (EN)c2000d2014  a978-3-11-023857-0  DGBA Backlist Complete English Language 2000-2014 P